{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"This is your conference,"},{"time":3000,"text":"and I think you have a right to know a little bit right now, in this transition period,"},{"time":9000,"text":"about this guy who's going to be looking after it for you for a bit."},{"time":12000,"text":"So, I'm just going to grab a chair here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":23000,"text":"Two years ago at TED, I think --"},{"time":30000,"text":"I've come to this conclusion --"},{"time":32000,"text":"I think I may have been suffering from a strange delusion."},{"time":35000,"text":"I think that I may have believed unconsciously,"},{"time":41000,"text":"then, that I was kind of a business hero."},{"time":47000,"text":"I had this company that I'd spent 15 years building. It's called Future;"},{"time":53000,"text":"it was a magazine publishing company."},{"time":55000,"text":"It had recently gone public"},{"time":57000,"text":"and the market said that it was apparently worth two billion dollars,"},{"time":61000,"text":"a number I didn't really understand."},{"time":63000,"text":"A magazine I'd recently launched called Business 2.0"},{"time":69000,"text":"was fatter than a telephone directory,"},{"time":71000,"text":"busy pumping hot air into the bubble."},{"time":74000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":76000,"text":"And I was the 40 percent owner of a dotcom"},{"time":82000,"text":"that was about to go public and no doubt be worth billions more."},{"time":85000,"text":"And all this had come from nothing."},{"time":88000,"text":"Fifteen years earlier, I was a science journalist who people just laughed at"},{"time":93000,"text":"when I said, \"I really would like to start my own computer magazine.\""},{"time":98000,"text":"And 15 years later, there are 100 of them"},{"time":102000,"text":"and 2,000 people on staff and it was just such heady times."},{"time":108000,"text":"The date was February 2000."},{"time":111000,"text":"I thought the little graph of my business life"},{"time":114000,"text":"that kind of looked a bit like Moore's Law --"},{"time":116000,"text":"ever upward and to the right -- it was going to go on forever."},{"time":118000,"text":"I mean, it had to. Right? I was in for quite a surprise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":127000,"text":"The dotcom, ironically called Snowball,"},{"time":130000,"text":"was the very last consumer web company to go public"},{"time":133000,"text":"the next month before NASDAQ exploded, and I entered 18 months of business hell."},{"time":144000,"text":"I watched everything that I'd built crumbling,"},{"time":150000,"text":"and it looked like all this stuff was going to die"},{"time":152000,"text":"and 15 years work would have come for nothing."},{"time":155000,"text":"And it was gut wrenching."},{"time":157000,"text":"It took eight years of blood, sweat and tears to reach 350 employees,"},{"time":164000,"text":"something which I was very proud of in the business."},{"time":167000,"text":"February 2001 -- in one day we laid off 350 people,"},{"time":172000,"text":"and before the bloodshed was finished, 1,000 people had lost their jobs"},{"time":176000,"text":"from my companies. I felt sick."},{"time":180000,"text":"I watched my own net worth falling"},{"time":186000,"text":"by about a million dollars a day, every day, for 18 months."},{"time":193000,"text":"And worse than that, far worse than that,"},{"time":195000,"text":"my sense of self-worth was kind of evaporating."},{"time":199000,"text":"I was going around with this big sign on my forehead: \"LOSER.\""},{"time":204000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":205000,"text":"And I think what disgusts me more than anything, looking back,"},{"time":209000,"text":"is how the hell did I let my personal happiness"},{"time":213000,"text":"get so tied up with this business thing?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":218000,"text":"Well, in the end, we were able to save Future and Snowball,"},{"time":224000,"text":"but I was, at that point, ready to move on."},{"time":227000,"text":"And to cut a long story short, here's where I came to."},{"time":231000,"text":"And the reason I'm telling this story is that I believe, from many conversations,"},{"time":237000,"text":"that a lot of people in this room have been through a similar kind of rollercoaster --"},{"time":242000,"text":"emotional rollercoaster -- in the last couple years."},{"time":245000,"text":"This has been a big, big transition time,"},{"time":248000,"text":"and I believe that this conference can play a big part for all of us"},{"time":255000,"text":"in taking us forward to the next stage to whatever's next."},{"time":258000,"text":"The theme next year is re-birth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261000,"text":"It was at the same TED two years ago"},{"time":265000,"text":"when Richard and I reached an agreement on the future of TED."},{"time":269000,"text":"And at about the same time, and I think partly because of that,"},{"time":273000,"text":"I started doing something that I'd forgotten about in my business focus:"},{"time":278000,"text":"I started to read again."},{"time":281000,"text":"And I discovered that while I'd been busy playing business games,"},{"time":286000,"text":"there'd been this incredible revolution in so many areas of interest:"},{"time":291000,"text":"cosmology to psychology to evolutionary psychology to anthropology"},{"time":297000,"text":"to ... all this stuff had changed."},{"time":299000,"text":"And the way in which you could think about us as a species"},{"time":304000,"text":"and us as a planet had just changed so much, and it was incredibly exciting."},{"time":308000,"text":"And what was really most exciting --"},{"time":310000,"text":"and I think Richard Wurman discovered this at least 20 years before I did --"},{"time":315000,"text":"was that all this stuff is connected."},{"time":319000,"text":"It's connected; it all hooks into each other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322000,"text":"We talk about this a lot,"},{"time":324000,"text":"and I thought about trying to give an example of this. So, just one example:"},{"time":327000,"text":"Madame de Gaulle, the wife of the French president,"},{"time":334000,"text":"was famously asked once, \"What do you most desire?\""},{"time":337000,"text":"And she answered, \"A penis.\""},{"time":341000,"text":"And when you think about it, it's very true:"},{"time":344000,"text":"what we all most desire is a penis --"},{"time":347000,"text":"or \"happiness\" as we say in English."},{"time":350000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":360000,"text":"And something ... good luck with that one in the Japanese translation room."},{"time":368000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":370000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":375000,"text":"But something as basic as happiness,"},{"time":379000,"text":"which 20 years ago would have been just something for discussion"},{"time":382000,"text":"in the church or mosque or synagogue,"},{"time":385000,"text":"today it turns out that there's dozens of TED-like questions"},{"time":389000,"text":"that you can ask about it, which are really interesting."},{"time":392000,"text":"You can ask about what causes it biochemically:"},{"time":395000,"text":"neuroscience, serotonin, all that stuff."},{"time":397000,"text":"You can ask what are the psychological causes of it:"},{"time":401000,"text":"nature? Nurture? Current circumstance?"},{"time":404000,"text":"Turns out that the research done on that is absolutely mind-blowing."},{"time":407000,"text":"You can view it as a computing problem, an artificial intelligence problem:"},{"time":412000,"text":"do you need to incorporate"},{"time":414000,"text":"some sort of analog of happiness into a computer brain to make it work properly?"},{"time":419000,"text":"You can view it in sort of geopolitical terms"},{"time":423000,"text":"and say, why is it that a billion people on this planet"},{"time":427000,"text":"are so desperately needy that they have no possibility of happiness,"},{"time":433000,"text":"and whereas almost all the rest of them,"},{"time":435000,"text":"regardless of how much money they have -- whether it's two dollars a day or whatever --"},{"time":439000,"text":"are almost equally happy on average?"},{"time":444000,"text":"Or you can view it as an evolutionary psychology kind of thing:"},{"time":449000,"text":"did our genes invent this as a kind of trick"},{"time":453000,"text":"to get us to behave in certain ways? The ant's brain, parasitized,"},{"time":457000,"text":"to make us behave in certain ways so that our genes would propagate?"},{"time":460000,"text":"Are we the victims of a mass delusion?"},{"time":462000,"text":"And so on, and so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464000,"text":"To understand even something as important to us as happiness,"},{"time":468000,"text":"you kind of have to branch off in all these different directions,"},{"time":471000,"text":"and there's nowhere that I've discovered -- other than TED --"},{"time":477000,"text":"where you can ask that many questions in that many different directions."},{"time":482000,"text":"And so, it's the profound thing that Richard talks about:"},{"time":485000,"text":"to understand anything, you just need to understand the little bits;"},{"time":489000,"text":"a little bit about everything that surrounds it."},{"time":491000,"text":"And so, gradually over these three days,"},{"time":493000,"text":"you start off kind of trying to figure out,"},{"time":495000,"text":"\"Why am I listening to all this irrelevant stuff?\""},{"time":498000,"text":"And at the end of the four days,"},{"time":500000,"text":"your brain is humming and you feel energized, alive and excited,"},{"time":505000,"text":"and it's because all these different bits have been put together."},{"time":508000,"text":"It's the total brain experience, we're going to ..."},{"time":510000,"text":"it's the mental equivalent of the full body massage."},{"time":512000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":513000,"text":"Every mental organ addressed. It really is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":518000,"text":"Enough of the theory, Chris. Tell us what you're actually going to do, all right?"},{"time":522000,"text":"So, I will. Here's the vision for TED."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525000,"text":"Number one: do nothing. This thing ain't broke, so I ain't gonna fix it."},{"time":533000,"text":"Jeff Bezos kindly remarked to me,"},{"time":536000,"text":"\"Chris, TED is a really great conference."},{"time":539000,"text":"You're going to have to fuck up really badly to make it bad.\""},{"time":542000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":546000,"text":"So, I gave myself the job title of TED Custodian for a reason,"},{"time":555000,"text":"and I will promise you right here and now"},{"time":557000,"text":"that the core values that make TED special are not going to be interfered with."},{"time":561000,"text":"Truth, curiosity, diversity, no selling, no corporate bullshit,"},{"time":572000,"text":"no bandwagoning, no platforms."},{"time":577000,"text":"Just the pursuit of interest, wherever it lies,"},{"time":582000,"text":"across all the disciplines that are represented here."},{"time":583000,"text":"That's not going to be changed at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":589000,"text":"Number two: I am going to put together"},{"time":591000,"text":"an incredible line up of speakers for next year."},{"time":594000,"text":"The time scale on which TED operates is just fantastic"},{"time":597000,"text":"after coming out of a magazine business with monthly deadlines."},{"time":601000,"text":"There's a year to do this, and already --"},{"time":603000,"text":"I hope to show you a bit later --"},{"time":605000,"text":"there's 25 or so terrific speakers signed up for next year."},{"time":610000,"text":"And I'm getting fantastic help from the community;"},{"time":613000,"text":"this is just such a great community. And combined, our contacts"},{"time":616000,"text":"reach pretty much everyone who's interesting in the country, if not the planet."},{"time":622000,"text":"It's true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":624000,"text":"Number three: I do want to, if I can, find a way"},{"time":631000,"text":"of extending the TED experience throughout the year a little bit."},{"time":634000,"text":"And one key way that we're going to do this is to introduce this book club."},{"time":639000,"text":"Books kind of saved me in the last couple years,"},{"time":645000,"text":"and that's a gift that I would like to pass on."},{"time":648000,"text":"So, when you sign up for TED2003, every six weeks you'll get a care package"},{"time":653000,"text":"with a book or two and a reason why they're linked to TED."},{"time":656000,"text":"They may well be by a TED speaker,"},{"time":658000,"text":"and so we can get the conversation going during the year"},{"time":661000,"text":"and come back next year having had the same intellectual, emotional journey."},{"time":667000,"text":"I think it will be great."}]},{"cues":[{"time":670000,"text":"And then, fourthly: I want to mention the Sapling Foundation,"},{"time":674000,"text":"which is the new owner of TED."},{"time":677000,"text":"What Sapling's ownership means is that all of the proceeds of TED"},{"time":679000,"text":"will go towards the causes that Sapling stands for."},{"time":686000,"text":"And more important, I think, the ideas that are exhibited and realized here"},{"time":694000,"text":"are ideas that the foundation can use, because there's fantastic synergy."},{"time":699000,"text":"Already, just in the last few days,"},{"time":701000,"text":"we've had so many people talking about stuff that they care about,"},{"time":704000,"text":"that they're passionate about, that can make a difference in the world,"},{"time":706000,"text":"and the idea of getting this group of people together --"},{"time":710000,"text":"some of the causes that we believe in,"},{"time":712000,"text":"the money that this conference can raise and the ideas --"},{"time":715000,"text":"I really believe that that combination will, over time, make a difference."},{"time":720000,"text":"I'm incredibly excited about that."},{"time":722000,"text":"In fact, I don't think, overall, that I've been as excited by anything ever in my life."},{"time":730000,"text":"I'm in this for the long run,"},{"time":733000,"text":"and I would be greatly honored and excited"},{"time":737000,"text":"if you'll come on this journey with me."}]}]}